[[ch01-biography]]
== Biography of Mybrid Wonderful

Note: This biography is limited to my qualifications for creating New Democracy.

Who am I to be proposing removing all nations from planet Earth? 

These are my bonafides.

New Democracy is a general study, not an expert focus. New Democracy touches on everything in life and therefore inventing New Democracy requires a general understanding of as many things as possible. In other words, a jack of all trades, a master of none as the saying goes.

These are my generalist bonafides.

I was born generally smart. It is always obnoxious to declare how smart one is I find. So I'm going to state my general intelligence as I'm an 'A' student among 'A' students. In other words, my university required an 'A' record to get into university and once  I was in I was an 'A' student among 'A' students.

My specific intelligence is general. This is tricky to explain. I'm neurodivergent. My brain focuses on things differently than is protrayed in popular culture like movies. My brain sees broad patterns where normal intelligence focuses on specific topics like mathematics, biology, art, or what have you.

My brain takes surface level topic patterns across all topics and then creates general patterns across multiple topics. This means I do not have a typical fascination or obsession with one topic. Instead I read on one topic, say anthropology, and then switch to another topic like biology. I've read on hundreds of different topics. This is what a generalist does. A generalist does pattern matching across many topics rather than focusing on one topic.

Generalists are rare. This is why you've probably never encountered one in ife or in entertainment.

However, I do have one topic I make a living at: software. I mean I have to make a living and software pays well.

When I was in grade school and high school we took personality tests based on aptitude of topics in order to help students decide on  possible occupations. I always tested heavily as an engineer. I am an engineer. What sets an engineer apart from other software developers is we spend more time testing than writing code. We are the engineer you want. We test elevators at three-thousand pound loads when the elevator is only sold for one-thousand pounds. I'm really good at mathematics and science.

But I'm also really good at all topics. Hence I was a straight 'A' student. However, I was straight 'A' because of interest and not just to have the grade level for opportunity.

Chai Tea Eggnog
Just using 1 cup of Chai Tea was too sweet for me, so I cut it in half.
1. 1 cup eggnog
2. 1/2 cup water
